watermelon feta salad   this might just be the fruit salad of the summer and a perfect addition to the spread this memorial day weekend its crunchy sweet sweet and refreshing  a true mouth party and so good the combination of watermelon feta mint is a classic and amazing on its own but when you add berries lime and pistachios into the mix it takes this salad to to a whole new level  you own the ratios here so feel free to modify this however way you want based on your own taste buds here is how i made it this makes a large partysized salad first start with a big base of watermelon chunks  i like to make these in smaller chunks about  inch cubes i went with about  cups of cubed watermelon add oz of blueberries and oz of raspberries to the mix add  cup fresh chopped mint add the zest of  large lime and squeeze the juice over the watermelon add  ounces of feta over the top  add two tablespoons of the highest quality olive oil you have add a couple small pinches of sea salt dont go overboard since feta is quite salty add a tablespoon or so of chile lime seasoning or tajin toss well and right before serving add  to  cup of freshly toasted pistachios give everything a really good mix gently so as to not crush the watermelon then give it a taste and modify as needed this is best served immediately and even better outside in the sunshine   enjoy lowcarb lowcarbrecipes watermelonsalad fruitsalad healthyrecipes healthyfoodshare goodmoodfood saladrecipe

career often referred to as the prince of darkness osbourne has had a profound influence on rock music and popular culture both as the frontman of black sabbath and as a solo artist osbournes early life was marked by economic hardship and a rebellious spirit growing up in a workingclass family in birmingham he faced numerous challenges including a troubled academic career and a series of odd jobs his passion for music emerged during his teenage years and he eventually joined the band earth which would later become black sabbath in  black sabbath was formed with osbourne as the lead vocalist alongside guitarist tony iommi bassist geezer butler and drummer bill ward the bands selftitled debut album released in  is often credited with pioneering heavy metal music black sabbaths dark heavy sound and osbournes distinctive voice set the stage for a new genre and influenced countless bands that followed black sabbaths  release paranoid further cemented their place in rock history with iconic tracks like iron man war pigs and the title track paranoid the albums success solidified osbournes reputation as a leading figure in the heavy metal genre his theatrical stage presence and powerful vocals became defining characteristics of the bands performances despite the bands success osbournes tenure with black sabbath was marked by internal conflicts and his own struggles with substance abuse the pressures of fame and the lifestyle associated with it took a toll on osbourne leading to his departure from the band in  his departure was a significant turning point both for him and for black sabbath who continued to have success with different lineups in  ozzy osbourne launched his solo career with the release of blizzard of ozz an album that introduced a new chapter in his career the album featured hit songs like crazy train and mr crowley showcasing osbournes ability to blend melodic elements with his heavy metal roots the success of the album marked the beginning of osbournes successful solo career and established him as a major force in rock music osbournes solo career continued to thrive throughout the s and s with a series of successful albums including diary of a madman  and no more tears  his music during this period maintained his heavy metal edge while also exploring new themes and styles hits like mama im coming home and no more tears became staples of his live performances despite ongoing health issues and various personal challenges including his battle with parkinsons disease osbourne has continued to tour and record new music his influence on heavy metal and rock music remains significant and his contributions to the genre have been recognized with numerous awards and honors ozzy osbournes impact on music and culture is profound he is often credited with shaping the sound of heavy metal and influencing countless artists who have followed in his footsteps his career marked by both remarkable achievements and notable controversies has established him as one of rocks most enduring and iconic figures overall ozzy osbournes legacy is characterized by his innovative approach to heavy metal his largerthanlife persona
